## Async Patterns

### HTTP clients — always use AsyncClient, always use context manager

```python
# Good
async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=10.0) as client:
    resp = await client.get(url, params=params)
    resp.raise_for_status()
    return resp.json()

# Wrong — sync requests in async code blocks the event loop
import requests
resp = requests.get(url)
```

### Background tasks — always track them

```python
# Good — tracked, can be awaited or cancelled
class AppState:
    _tasks: set[asyncio.Task] = set()

    def create_task(self, coro):
        task = asyncio.create_task(coro)
        self._tasks.add(task)
        task.add_done_callback(self._tasks.discard)
        return task

# Wrong — fire and forget, silently swallows errors
asyncio.create_task(some_coro())
```

### Timeouts — always set them

```python
# Good
result = await asyncio.wait_for(skill.execute(tool_name, params), timeout=30.0)

# Wrong — hangs forever if skill hangs
result = await skill.execute(tool_name, params)
```

