## Adding a New Skill (Checklist)

1. Create `backend/skills/<name>/` directory
2. Write `skill.toml` with `[skill]` and `[skill.permissions]` sections
3. Implement `main.py` with a `BaseSkill` subclass
4. Tool names must be lowercase snake_case: `get_weather`, `search_web`
5. Descriptions must be imperative, precise, LLM-readable
6. `execute()` returns `SkillResult` — never raises
7. `health_check()` returns `bool` — fast, no I/O
8. Write tests in `backend/tests/test_skills/test_builtin/test_{name}.py`
9. Sentinel will hot-reload — no restart needed

